body:
It affects more than GridView. Actually it affects any dropDownList, listBox and may be widgets based on them if options are unlucky and contain item with 0 key. Consider the following code:

```php
echo Html::dropDownList(
    'test_dropdown',
    '',
    ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
    ['prompt' => 'Select']
);
echo '<br/><br/>';

echo Html::listBox(
    'test_list_box',
    '',
    ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
    ['prompt' => 'Select']
);
echo '<br/><br/>';

echo \kartik\select2\Select2::widget(
    [
        'name' => 'test_select2',
        'value' => '',
        'data' => ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
        'options' => ['prompt' => 'Select'],
    ]
);
```

Prior to 2.0.46:
![old](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3766212/186474254-8ceb427e-6cc2-4960-869f-33e563301a2e.png)
Since 2.0.46:
![new](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3766212/186474397-1ba4be6b-2fe4-4e5f-993b-ef71fe24de4b.png)

It seems to be we have to add "strict" everywhere to have adequate UI:

```php
echo Html::dropDownList(
    'test_dropdown',
    '',
    ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
    ['prompt' => 'Select', 'strict' => true]
);
echo '<br/><br/>';

echo Html::listBox(
    'test_list_box',
    '',
    ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
    ['prompt' => 'Select', 'strict' => true]
);
echo '<br/><br/>';

echo \kartik\select2\Select2::widget(
    [
        'name' => 'test_select2',
        'value' => '',
        'data' => ['1' => 'Yes', '0' => 'No'],
        'options' => ['prompt' => 'Select', 'strict' => true],
    ]
);
```
